<inglise> The Commission will implement the Programme. </inglise>
<eesti> Programmi rakendab komisjon. </eesti>
<inglise> It may, to this end, call upon independent consultants and technical assistance offices to be selected, after a call for tenders, on the basis of their expertise in the sector, experience acquired in the MEDIA II programme, or other experience acquired in this area. </inglise>
<eesti> Selleks v&otilde;ib ta kasutada selliste s&otilde;ltumatute konsultantide ja tehnilise abi b&uuml;roode abi, kes valitakse p&auml;rast pakkumismenetlust l&auml;htudes nende asjatundlikkusest asjaomases sektoris, programmi MEDIA II raames omandatud kogemustest v&otilde;i muudest k&otilde;nealuses valdkonnas omandatud kogemustest. </eesti>
<inglise> The technical assistance will be financed by the Programme's budget. </inglise>
<eesti> Tehnilist abi rahastatakse programmi eelarvest. </eesti>
<inglise> The Commission may also conclude, in accordance with the procedure referred to in Article 8(2), partnerships for operations with specialist bodies, including those which have been set up under other European initiatives such as Audiovisual Eureka, EURIMAGES and the European Audiovisual Observatory in order to implement joint measures that meet the Programme objectives in the field of promotion. </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjon v&otilde;ib artikli 8 l&otilde;ikes 2 osutatud korras s&otilde;lmida partnerlepinguid erialaste ettev&otilde;tetega, kaasa arvatud nendega, mis on loodud muude Euroopa algatuste, n&auml;iteks audiovisuaalse Eureka, EURIMAGESi ja Euroopa Audiovisuaalsektori Vaatluskeskuse raames, et rakendada programmi m&uuml;&uuml;giedendamisvaldkonna eesm&auml;rkidele vastavaid &uuml;hismeetmeid. </eesti>
<inglise> The Commission will make the final selection of the beneficiaries of the Programme and decide on the financial support to be granted, in accordance with Article 8, on the basis of preparatory work conducted by the technical assistance offices. </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjon valib l&otilde;plikult v&auml;lja programmi toetusesaajad ja otsustab antava rahalise toetuse &uuml;le vastavalt artiklile 8 l&auml;htudes tehnilise abi b&uuml;roode tehtud eelt&ouml;&ouml;st. </eesti>
<inglise> It will give grounds for its decisions to applicants for Community support and ensure the transparency of implementation of the programme. </inglise>
<eesti> Ta esitab oma otsuste p&otilde;hjendused &uuml;henduse toetuse taotlejatele ja tagab programmi rakendamise l&auml;bipaistvuse. </eesti>
<inglise> In order to execute the Programme and, in particular, evaluate the projects benefiting from Programme funding and networking activities, the Commission will draw on recognised, independent audiovisual experts in the fields of development, production, distribution and promotion, who are, where necessary, proficient in the area of the management of rights, especially in the new digital environment. </inglise>
<eesti> Selleks et programm ellu viia ja eelk&otilde;ige, et hinnata programmi rahastamist ja loodud koost&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;rke kasutavaid projekte, kasutatakse selliste arendamise, tootmise, turustamise ja m&uuml;&uuml;giedendamisvaldkonnas tegutsevate s&otilde;ltumatute audiovisuaalsektori spetsialistide abi, kes oskavad vajaduse korral &otilde;igusi teostada, seda eelk&otilde;ige uues digitaalses keskkonnas. </eesti>
<inglise> 2.3.2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2.3.2. </eesti>
<inglise> The Commission will take the necessary steps to provide information on the opportunities offered by the Programme, and will ensure its promotion. </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjon v&otilde;tab vajalikud meetmed, et anda teavet programmi raames pakutavate v&otilde;imaluste kohta ja tagada sellega programmi tutvustamine. </eesti>
<inglise> The Commission will also provide via the Internet comprehensive information concerning the support arrangements available under the European Union's policies which are of relevance to the audiovisual sector. </inglise>
<eesti> Lisaks sellele annab komisjon Interneti vahendusel ulatuslikku teavet Euroopa Liidu poliitika raames k&auml;ttesaadava toetuse s&uuml;steemi kohta, mis on audiovisuaalsektori puhul oluline. </eesti>
<inglise> In particular, the Commission and the Member States will take the necessary steps, by continuing with the activities of the network of MEDIA Desks and Antennae and ensuring that their professional skills are enhanced, in order to: </inglise>
<eesti> Eelk&otilde;ige astuvad komisjon ja liikmesriigid vajalikke samme seel&auml;bi, et j&auml;tkavad MEDIA- infopunktide ja harukontorite v&otilde;rgu tegevust ja tagavad nende erialaste oskuste edendamise, et: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) inform professionals in the audiovisual sector of the various support arrangements available under European Union policies; </inglise>
<eesti> a) teavitada audiovisuaalsektori spetsialiste Euroopa Liidu poliitika raames kasutatavatest eri toetuste s&uuml;steemidest; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) publicise and promote the Programme; </inglise>
<eesti> b) programmi reklaamida ja selle olemasolust teavitada; </eesti>
<inglise> (c) encourage maximum participation in the Programme's activities by professionals; </inglise>
<eesti> c) toetada spetsialistide maksimaalset osalemist programmi t&ouml;&ouml;s; </eesti>
<inglise> (d) assist professionals with the presentation of projects in response to calls for proposals; </inglise>
<eesti> d) abistada spetsialiste ettepanekute esitamise &uuml;leskutsete peale projektide esitamisel; </eesti>
<inglise> (e) foster transborder cooperation between professionals; </inglise>
<eesti> e) soodustada spetsialistide piiri&uuml;lest koost&ouml;&ouml;d; </eesti>
<inglise> (f) liaise between the various support bodies in the Member States with a view to ensuring that Programme activities complement national support measures. </inglise>
<eesti> f) &uuml;hendada liikmesriikide eri toetusorganeid selleks, et tagada programmi meetmete ja liikmesriikide toetusmeetmete vastastikune t&auml;iendavus. </eesti>
 